n cancer cells, highlighting its potential as an anticancer agent. Further research is needed to fully understand the health benefits of Malaxis corymbosa and to explore its potential applications in medicine.", "parts": "Malaxis corymbosa is primarily known for its medicinal properties, although specific information regarding its medicinal parts could not be found.", "intro": "Malaxis corymbosa, also known as the orchid flag or Malaxis, is a type of terrestrial orchid native to tropical regions of Central and South America. Traditionally, the plant has been used in folk medicine to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues, due to its potential anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. The bioactive constituents of Malaxis corymbosa include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In herbal medicine, Malaxis corymbosa is often used to make teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are used to treat a range of health issues, although more research is needed to confirm its efficacy and safety."}